Deux euphoniums duettants se lancent sous les feux de la rampe dans ce morceau léger et insouciant. Les deux solistes ont l'occasion de démontrer leurs talents musicaux tandis que l'orchestre les accompagnant leur fournit le support nécessaire. Bref,  Happy Deal  confère un éclat de bonne humeur votre répertoire

Mambo Americano  a été écrit en hommage aux compositeurs de l’ ge d’or du mambo. Des compositions comme celles de Pérez Prado, ou comme  Mambo  tiré de  West Side Story  de Leonard Bernstein des années 1950, sont désormais établis dans notre monde de musique contemporain et c’est précisément cette époque qui est évoquée pour le public dans  Mambo Americano  !

Robert Buckley a pris une approche rhapsodique pour cette version du célèbre  Sonnent les cloches , mêlant des idées originales avec la mélodie connue. Chaque registre de l’orchestre aura l’occasion de briller dans ce numéro de fête éblouissant et élaboré.

The word nexus is defined as a tie or link between people and events. Nexus for solo trumpet and band includes several links between composer James Curnow and educator Alfred Watkins, to whom the work is dedicated. A well-knowntheme (particularly to Mr. Watkins' students) is drawn upon as the piece utilizes two primary musical settings - an energetic and agile scherzo that appears in the beginning and again at the
sous_titre: for Solo Trumpet, Winds and Percussion

description: This work for advanced band was commissioned by the Tennessee Valley Winds to celebrate the group's 30th anniversary. The piece begins quietly with clarinet solo, then quickly moves to a celebratory section in 12/8 meter. The mainmelody is stated in many different voices as it steadily builds to a moment of controlled frenzy. A brief lyrical section features an expressive style and also a moment of glory for the

Here is a unique setting of two holiday favorites set in a smooth Latin style. Bells Over Bethlehem (Andalusian Carol) uses a mixture of unison and harmony sections as the melody is passed around the band. O Tannenbaum has acontemporary flavor and utilizes interesting chord progressions. Fresh!

Premiered by Maestro Eugene Migliaro Corporon conducting the National Honor Band of America, this spectacular memorial for renowned band director Charles Campbell will surround your students and audiences in layers of emotion. Expressive moments upon moments allow the ensemble to follow their musical instincts, gaining an aesthetic reward each time. Typical of performances, the work fades into introspective silence,

Each of the five movements of this innovative work is designed to invoke a particular type of emotion associated with leadership. Courage is stately in nature and written in a marcato style. Vision is playful in character andfocuses on mixed meters as well as mixed emotions. The lyrical and sensitive Compassion is meant to stir the soul, while the contrasting Selflessness offers some of the most intense and demanding

Stephen Sondheim's masterful Broadway musical struck a resounding chord with a new audience thanks to the recent movie adaptation and all-star cast. This impressive and well-paced medley for band includes  Into the Woods, Giants in the Sky, Children Will Listen, Last Midnight , and  No One Is Alone .

Long walks in the mountains of Telemark has inspired the composer to write this original suite for young bands. The mountains are impressive and dramatic, but also make you feel calm and with a sense of freedom. The 4 movements are a praise to thisbeautiful nature.

This Christmas psalm is famous all over the world and especially in Europe. It is likely that the melody is more than 600 years old. Many famous composers have written their own harmonics and versions of the psalm.  This arrangement isbased on two different harmonics; The first and third verse is based on the harmonics by Michael Praetorius while the second verse is based on the harmonics of Johann Sebastian Bach.

No matter how old you are, the familiar melodies from this popular television series never fail to raise a smile. Here's a delightful and entertaining medley for young players that includes Sesame Street Theme, C Is for Cookie,Bein' Green, and Sing.  ScorePlay - click to view score with recording.

Legend of Old Abe is a marvelously descriptive work for young bands thattakes the listener on a journey of Old Abe's exploits. From a peaceful and serene opening the work progresses through the sounds of conflict and battle. The mood turns reflective and then

Glistening chords, soaring melodies, broad fanfares and gorgeous chorales will fill your concert hall with this evocative work. Best of all, From Gold sounds much harder than it actually is. Mr. Hazo's background as a musiceducator is evident in how quickly directors and students will get to the music making. Written entirely in B-flat with few accidentals, the runs are split between instruments for playability, and

Commissioned for the Shelby County (AL) All-County Honor Band, this work draws its title from the Cahaba River, the longest free-flowing river in Alabama. The outward dances are lively and busy, reflecting the growth andprosperity of the region, while the middle section is more contemplative, portraying the area's scenic natural beauty. Magnificently scored and effectively paced. Dur: 6:45

Composed in 2014, this piece commemorates anniversaries of important events in American history: the writing of The Star Spangled Banner in 1814, the beginning of World War 1 in 1914, and the Allied invasion of Nazi-occupiedFrance in 1944. The primary theme is original, with motives from America the Beautiful and The Star Spangled Banner interwoven throughout. A well-conceived and skillful lyric treatment for the
titre: O'er the Land of the Free

description: Percy Grainger composed this work for “six hands at one piano” in 1902, and subsequently he began a version for percussion ensemble that was never completed. Using sketches of this incomplete arrangement, Preston Hazzard has created a unique setting for concert band. The transparent and delicate lilting nature of the original work comes through in this appealing arrangement for winds and percussion.
Night is a calm, slow piece of music. Almost like an ancient chant.

This piece is about the anxiety of going to the doctor, the effect of taking too many pills, and the frustration of not getting the proper medication! Three movements: I - At the Doctor II - Under the Influence III - Backto the Doctor To the conductor: This piece present challenges regarding accidentals and dissonant chords but consists for the most part of simpler rhythms and texture. There is much use of repeating

This character piece was composed for a competition held in 1962 by the Norwegian Band Federation. Three prices were awarded and Geirr Tveitt won all of them. “The Old Mill on the Brook” was awarded second price after the three-movement work “Sinfonietta de Soffiatori”. After this competition, “”The Old Mill on the Brook” is the most performed of all pieces Tveitt wrote for band. It has a special fullness, portraying
titre: The Old Mill on the Brook

description: Chanson DAmour ("Song of love") is a popular song written by Wayne Shanklin. It became a Top Ten hit in 1958 performed by Art and Dotty Todd. The married couple were the resident act at the Chapman Park Hotel in Los Angeles at the moment. A1977 recording by the Manhattan Transfer was an international hit, reaching no 1 in the UK Singles Chart and in Australia. The recording sold 1,8 million albums in Europe alone.

The popular Norwegian singer/songwriter Jonas Fjeld released the single "Angels in the Snow" in 1989. It was one of the tracks on the record album ”Svært nok for meg” (“Big enough for me”) which was released later the same year. The album became ahuge success, topping the charts for several weeks. “Angels in the Snow” is also released on other albums, both as concert recordings and studio recording. This arrangement

In November 2014, the conductor Peter Szilvay, on behalf of Christiania Wind Ensemble (Oslo), commissioned a piece from me. He was looking for a quite short piece of music, effective, intense and dance-like.He mentioned A Short Ride in a Fast Machine by John Adams, and I answered his request by writing my piece, Dirty Dancing. It is a rather easy listening piece that play with riffs and rhythms.Szilvay did not

In this piece for second-year players, Paul Murtha masterfully adapts the traditional military march form for young musicians. The first strain is carried by trumpets and upper woodwinds, while the low brass take the lead on thesecond strain. After a brief percussion break, the legato trio melody features the woodwind section. A call and response breakstrain is followed by the full band on the rousing finish. Keep

The music of Handel is considered the culmination of the Baroque period of music history, and his Water Music (1717) has endured in popularity for nearly 300 years! Performed from a barge traveling on the River Thames, King GeorgeI is said to have liked the music so much that he ordered it repeated several times. Originally three suites each consisting of multiple movements, Johnnie Vinson has skillfully adapted this

Famed bandmaster Arthur Delamont always programmed a hymn in his concerts and  Memento  is an homage to that proud tradition. Starting with a simple and reverent solo trumpet and introducing other brass instruments one by one, the introduction has the sound of a brass band. The woodwinds join in and, with the use of rich textures and dynamic scoring, the work builds to a powerful climax and then resolves once again
sous_titre: Second Movement of A Tribute to Arthur Delamont

description: Featuring a dynamic yet easy melody, this powerful piece for first-year players will sound great with limited rehearsal time and help give your students confidence. Every section of the band has interesting parts to play, and thepercussion provide a solid foundation in addition to short feature spots.

Inspired by an exhibition of historic Peruvian art, Kingdom of the Sun and Moon takes us on a mythical journey reflecting the ancient Inca Empire. This imaginary movie score uses modal melodies, exotic percussion and dramaticorchestration to create an epic music experience. In cinematic style, this work opens with a panoramic picture of the great Inca city of Machu Picchu and ends with a colorful procession towards
titre: Kingdom of the Sun and Moon

description: Set in a jazzy medium swing style, Luther Henderson created an unforgettable setting of  Rudolph  for the Canadian Brass. Maintaining the clever scoring devices and “schtick” of the original, Michael Brown's skillful adaptation for concert band is sure to be as much fun for the audience as it is the players.

In this high-energy arrangement of the signature hit from the “Godfather of Soul,” the low brass start out on the theme with the band answering with the familiar riffs. The saxes are featured on the “breakdown” section along with the rest of the woodwinds. A nice blast of nostalgia for any audience.

Cette ballade intemporelle de Porgy & Bess de Gershwin est arrangée ici pour de jeunes formations dans un style de blues et swing. Robert Longfield utilise de riches harmonies, une orchestration variée et un accompagnement créatif tout au long de cet arrangement qui fera plaisir au public de chaque ge.

Of all the James Bond movies through the years,  Live and Let Die , recorded by Paul McCartney and Wings, provided one of the most dynamic and powerful theme songs. Mixing a variety of styles from pop ballad, reggae, to driving rock, this explosive arrangement will light up any concert stage.

Here's the tender ballad from Disney's beloved film Mary Poppins nicely arranged for second year players. The clarinets are featured initially, later joined by the trumpets, and even the low brass get their turn with the melody. Sure to be enjoyed by students and parents alike.

Enregistré par le trio dynamique composé de Jessie J, Ariana Grande et Nicki Minaj, ce tube cool de musique pop a un tempo rapide et des mélodies vives avec un accompagnement stop-time ainsi que tout plein d’énergie !

Featuring a signature bass line riff and powerful rock beat, this Ozzy Osbourne hit remains one of the classic rock anthems of all time. The trumpets take center stage at the beginning, and are then joined by the rest of the ensemble in this great-sounding arrangement for young players.

The distinctive theme for this popular television series is both haunting and rhythmically intense. In creating this very effective adaptation for band, Robert Longfield skillfully trades the active background figure from sectionto section, and contrasts this with the flowing lyric melody.

L’emploi (ou l’usage excessif) du cencerro (« cowbell ») dans la musique pop des années 70 fut dépeinte dans le sketch humoristique sur Saturday Night Live avec Christopher Walken et Will Ferrell. Voici un medley amusant de tubes chargés de cencerro tel que  (Don’t Fear) The Reaper  ,  Low Rider ,  Drive My Car  et  Oye Como Va . Pour plus de spectacle, conviez un invité (dignitaire local, directeur, etc.) sur le
With its distinctive reggae beat and dance-like percussion groove, this contemporary hit recorded by the group Magic! adapts nicely for band in this effective setting for young players.

With a catchy riff and infectious beat, this hit from 2007 has become a widely popular line dance at clubs, parties, and even wedding receptions. This solid arrangement cleverly passes fragments of the melody from section to section accompanied by the driving dance pulse.

Letter from Sado is an exciting piece for young band designed to draw out the musicality in young players. With a focus on interpretation of an ancient haiku poem with natural imagery, performers are invited to become decision makers about specific sections in the music. Their decisions include ideas regarding tempo, dynamics and articulation in order to represent a wild stormy sea and a still starry night. Free

Commissioned to celebrate the sesquicentennial of the state of West Virginia, Forever Free incorporates indigenous elements of the state's musical heritage, capturing a robust and celebratory spirit. Cast in a single movement inthree sections, the title is inspired by the state motto, Montani semper liberi (Mountaineeers forever free). The work is unified at the outset and closing by a ceremonial fanfare that is

Michael Oare's Escapade is a mischievous and fun-filled romp for beginning players. Using creative effects including trombone glisses, slide whistles, mouthpiece screeches, and dissonant crunches, your players will have blast withthis, and the audience will too!

Ce tube de l’artiste Meghan Trainor présente une mélodie accrocheuse et optimiste ainsi que même un soupçon de doo-wop par moments. Cet arrangement convaincant pour de jeunes orchestres donne une importance particulière aux instruments jouant la ligne de basse, pourtant chaque section de l'orchestre joue la mélodie tôt ou tard. S rement facile apprendre et amusant jouer.

Originally composed for the 2011 film  Captain America: The First Avenger , Alan Silvestri's dynamic and expansive theme has taken on a life of its own. Johnnie Vinson has skillfully retained the excitement of the original in this very playable version for young players.

Adoptant un format militaire,  Roman Juggernaut  décrit musicalement les formidables légions incarnant la puissance romaine. Avec ses percussions implacables et ses fanfares résonnantes, cette pièce évoque aisément le spectacle extraordinaired’un défilé de milliers de soldats.

Cette marche classique et raffinée du grand compositeur américain John Philip Sousa est la seule de son genre qui commence par une mesure en 6/8 pour passer ensuite une partie en 2/4. Jay Bocook a adapté cette passionnante marche pour ensemble dejeunes (ou moins jeunes !).
Cette pièce porte bien son titre de  Flash in the Pan!  (Feu de paille) avec des rythmes changeants, des passages dissonants audacieux et des percussions entraînantes qui viennent épicer la musique.

Dans  Ode to the Spirit of Man , James Curnow utilise le matériau thématique du 4e mouvement de la 9e Symphonie de Beethoven, le transformant en un kaléidoscope éblouissant d’imagination en y joignant  Alla Marcia, Scherzo, Andantemaestoso  et pour finir, l’ Ode la joie .
titre: Ode to the Spirit of Man

description: Les deux premières phrases de l’oeuvre  Three Colonial Moments  racontent l’histoire de deux légendes américaines alors que la troisième phrase a été écrite autour d’une danse issue de l’état de Virginie. Riche en diversité stylistique etsonore, c’est une oeuvre attrayante pour tout concert ou festival.

Voici une pièce pleine d’énergie qui donnera aux jeunes percussionnistes l’occasion de briller. James Curnow emploie une grande diversité d’instruments et d’effets de percussion dans ce tour de force exubérant.

Composée pour un festival d’orchestres d’harmonie Duluth, Minnesota, et pouvant suggérer une descente de ski alpin ou une poursuite en motoneige travers les bois,  Due North  est une ouverture rapide écrite entièrement sur un même tempo.Diverses ambiances sont exprimées, tandis que thèmes et idées musicales passent d’un pupitre un autre. Tout au long, les percussions entretiennent une pulsion rythmique acharnée.

March to Concord  commémore l’un des premiers combats et l’un des plus décisifs de la Guerre d’Indépendance américaine. Rick Kirby honore cet événement historique avec une composition de nature héro que mêlant rythme, puissance et variété.

Dans ce magnifique et authentique pot-pourri américain, tous les pupitres de l’orchestre jouent la mélodie un moment donné. La pièce comprend des fragments de  The Battle Cry of Freedom, The Star Spangled Banner, Yankee Doodle, America theBeautiful, Chester  et  America .
titre: From Every Mountainside (A Salute to America)

description: Cette oeuvre impressionnante commence et se termine par un thème en fanfare puissant et fédérateur. La partie centrale est, quant elle, construite autour de rythmes modernes et de mélodies plus classiques - on y entend même un soupçon de  Jésusque ma joie demeure , donnant ainsi une sonorité intemporelle la pièce. Laissez-vous charmer par la tradition et la modernité de  Arrows  !

Intronisé au Rock and Roll Hall of Fame (Temple de la renommée du rock and roll) en 2000, Eric Clapton est considéré comme l’un des guitaristes les plus influents de tous les temps, son palmarès de tubes couvrant quatre décennies. Dans ce formidablemedley pour orchestre vent, Paul Murtha a adapté les meilleures chansons de Clapton pour une interprétation en concert, parmi lesquelles  Change the World, Forever Man,

Jefferson Forest Sketches  dépeint la beauté de cette forêt des Appalaches l’aube sur les montagnes, des panoramas extraordinaires et grandes étendues sauvages. Cette pièce descriptive se termine avec une sélection de danses populaires decette région splendide.

Cette “Carte postale d’Angleterre” décrit une ballade travers la campagne typiquement anglaise, avec des collines, des chaumières, des maisons pittoresques, des ch teaux et des églises. Tels des randonneurs, les musiciens égrènent un thèmemajestueux qui rappelle le son des ensembles de cuivres. Offrez, vos auditeurs, une vision panoramique de nos amis d’outre-Atlantique... So British !

Arctic Fire  dévoile différentes images du Nord, dans un style d’écriture plutôt cinématographique : les teintes flamboyantes des icebergs au coucher du soleil, l’éclat des lumières du Nord, le rouge des cornouillers sans oublier le caractèrefougueux des habitants de l’Arctique. La pièce évoque une série d’instantanés musicaux puis évolue travers un large éventail de textures stylistiques. Une oeuvre brillante,
sous_titre: 1st Movement of Portraits of the North

description: Adirondack Festival Overture  combine d’une manière fort sympathique des chansons originales et des airs traditionnels folk qui nous ont été transmis par des générations de musiciens vivant au coeur du parc Adirondack (États-Unis). Plus quesurprenant !

Composé en 1962,  Do You Hear What I Hear  est un chant de Noël qui peut se vanter d’avoir été interprété par une multitude d’artistes. Notons également qu’il occupe une place de choix dans la fameuse série télévisée  Glee . De quoi ravirpetits et grands !
titre: Do You Hear What I Hear

description: Composé par Kelly Clarkson, cet hymne rock est devenu un classique contemporain gr ce ses mélodies mémorables et une puissante pulsion rythmique. En voici une version impressionnante pour harmonie dans un arrangement solide sans grande difficulté.

Notamment chantée par les Celtic Woman, cette ravissante chanson enchaîne sur un style celtique, une charmante mélodie de Noël et le célèbre thème de Minuit, Chrétiens. Michael Brown nous livre un arrangement pour orchestre d’harmonie fidèle laversion originale.

Rassemblant des chansons interprétées par les Beatles lors de leur premier passage la télévision américaine, en 1964, et parues sur leur premier album sorti aux USA,  Meet the Beatles , voici un pot-pourri exubérant pour orchestre d’harmoniequi démontre l’attrait et la vigueur de ces premiers tubes. Comprend  I Want to Hold Your Hand, Till There Was You  et  All My Loving .
sous_titre: All My Loving - Till There Was You - I Want to Hold Your Hand

description: Cette composition représente l’apogée de la série de concertos de Satoshi Yagisawa, qui comprend aussi une  Suite concertante pour piano et orchestre , un  Concerto pour trompette , un  Concerto pour trombone , un  Concertino poursaxophone  et un  Concertino pour percussion solo et orchestre d’harmonie . En raison de sa grande popularité, le thème émouvant du deuxième mouvement, qui est intitulé  Intermezzo , est

C’est lors d’un séjour en Slavonie que le compositeur fut subjugué par la beauté de cette région. Il rassemble ses impressions dans quatre caractères : une danse lente exprimant l’élégance calme et mesurée, les fêtes quise déroulent le long de la Save, la rêverie qu’exhale la respectueuse passion de la nature tandis que le dernier caractère développe l’ambiance qui

Conçu en tant que pièce instrumentation variable,  Let It Go  offre également la possibilité de varier l’interprète de la partie solistique. Celle-ci pourra être chantée ou jouée par une Clarinette, un Saxophone alto, une Fl te ou uneTrompette. Ce merveilleux arrangement de la chanson phare de  La Reine des neiges , de Disney, apportera de la variété n’importe quel concert.

Enregistré par la chanteuse sensationnelle néo-zélandaise Lorde, et gagnant un Grammy® Award pour  Song of the Year  (chanson de l’année) en 2014, ce tube pop a un son unique et distinctif. Bien arrangé pour fanfare, vos musiciens seront s rs de demander jouer ce morceau.

Tirée de la comédie musicale  La Mélodie du bonheur , cette chanson aux mélodies inoubliables transmet un message éternel. Le bel arrangement pour orchestre harmonie de Robert Longfield s’apprend facilement, mais le résultat est riche etimpressionnant.
titre: Climb Ev'ry Mountain (from The Sound of Music)

description: Voici un hymne joyeux qui célèbre le temps de l’Avent et de Noël car il réunit deux incontournables :  Noel Nouvelet  et  The First Nowell , simplement appelé  Noël  en français. James Curnow utilise habilement une série de variationset de styles musicaux contrastés en tissant ces deux airs de manière attrayante et inspirée.

With its energetic impetus and imposing instrumentation, Concertino is certainly outstanding in the oeuvre of Árpád Balázs. Among his compositions for concert band, it is by far the most engaging and exacting work. Passing away and a will to live are simultaneously present in Concertino, which Árpád Balázs composed in memory of his beloved father. Its structure brings Liszt─s Hungarian Rhapsodies to mind: its solemn

Le chef-d’oeuvre de Harry Belafonte concernant le lien entre le feu, l’eau, les montagnes et l’esprit a été entendu, avec grand succès, dans la série télévisée  Les Muppets  en 1977. Expliquant que, gr ce la compréhension, nous pouvons tous «transformer le monde », cette chanson était une des préférées du créateur des Muppets. Fondé sur un rythme en 5/4 aux accents africains, voici un arrangement unique et percutant

Deux styles bien distincts se rencontrent dans cet arrangement plein d’entrain. Un morceau bluegrass bien connu en Amérique,  Angelina the Baker,  est adroitement combiné un air de danse celte ! Après une introduction fluide et lyrique, lesbourdons et les rythmes d’une gigue irlandaise emportent l´orchestre et son public dans une danse exubérante.

Crosslands  commence très doucement par une pastorale invitant la réflexion. Puis un thème audacieux joué par les trompettes et les cors s’installe. La pièce se termine par les doux rayons d’un coucher de soleil au dessus de l’océan. Unemerveilleuse oeuvre descriptive !

Robert Buckley s’est inspiré de ce très beau chant de Noël pour composer cette exceptionnelle fantaisie. La mélodie obsédante est habilement tissée travers une série de variantes stylistiques riches et variées. Chacun des pupitres interprètera tour de rôle la ligne mélodie de cette pièce enchanteresse.

Commissioned for the Shelby County (AL) All-County Honor Band, this work draws its title from the Cahaba River, the longest free-flowing river in Alabama. The outward dances are lively and busy, reflecting the growth andprosperity of the region, while the middle section is more contemplative, portraying the area's scenic natural beauty. Magnificently scored and effectively paced. Dur: 6:45

In this high-energy arrangement of the signature hit from the “Godfather of Soul,” the low brass start out on the theme with the band answering with the familiar riffs. The saxes are featured on the “breakdown” section along with the rest of the woodwinds. A nice blast of nostalgia for any audience.

sous_titre: Based on The Little Drummer Boy
The Love of Our Country, Love and Fame

description: Cette ballade intemporelle de Porgy & Bess de Gershwin est arrangée ici pour de jeunes formations dans un style de blues et swing. Robert Longfield utilise de riches harmonies, une orchestration variée et un accompagnement créatif tout au long de cet arrangement qui fera plaisir au public de chaque ge.

Adoptant un format militaire,  Roman Juggernaut  décrit musicalement les formidables légions incarnant la puissance romaine. Avec ses percussions implacables et ses fanfares résonnantes, cette pièce évoque aisément le spectacle extraordinaired’un défilé de milliers de soldats.

sous_titre: Mvt. 2 from Three Folk Song Settings for Band

description: Cette marche classique et raffinée du grand compositeur américain John Philip Sousa est la seule de son genre qui commence par une mesure en 6/8 pour passer ensuite une partie en 2/4. Jay Bocook a adapté cette passionnante marche pour ensemble dejeunes (ou moins jeunes !).

Composé en 1962,  Do You Hear What I Hear  est un chant de Noël qui peut se vanter d’avoir été interprété par une multitude d’artistes. Notons également qu’il occupe une place de choix dans la fameuse série télévisée  Glee . De quoi ravirpetits et grands !
titre: Do You Hear What I Hear
Two Variants on Dives and Lazarus

sous_titre: A Medley of Patriotic March Themes

description: Composé par Kelly Clarkson, cet hymne rock est devenu un classique contemporain gr ce ses mélodies mémorables et une puissante pulsion rythmique. En voici une version impressionnante pour harmonie dans un arrangement solide sans grande difficulté.

titre: At the Movies with Danny Elfman

description: Sean O’Loughlin vient confirmer avec cet arrangement qu’il est tout fait possible pour un orchestre d’harmonie, d’interpréter du Heavy-Metal. Ayant joué avec les plus grands musiciens de studio et fort de son expérience de compositeur, il nouslivre une pièceremarquable rassemblant :  The Trooper  (Iron Maiden),  Iron Man  (Black Sabbath),  Rock You Like a Hurricane  (Scorpions) et  Crazy Train  (Ozzy Osbourne).

Enregistré l’origine par Cee Lo Green et rendu encore plus populaire gr ce Gwyneth Paltrow et les acteurs de  Glee , ce titre bénéficie d’un arrangement solide et divertissant pour très jeunes musiciens.
sous_titre: As performed by Cee Lo Green

description: Enregistrée par Coldplay, cette belle ballade émouvante tirée de  The Hunger Games: Catching Fire  (Hunger Games : L’Embrasement) est la première composition originale écrite et enregistrée par le groupe spécifiquement pour un film.
sous_titre: from The Hunger Games: Catching Fire
titre: Atlas (from The Hunger Games: Catching Fire)

description: Écrit dans le style du boléro mexicain, ce classique latino des années quarante a toujours été populaire et a souvent été enregistré avec des paroles anglaises ou françaises, comme  Je te tiens sur mon coeur . La superbe version de RobertLongfield emploie de riches harmonies et offre un agréable changement d’ambiance.

Cette chanson succès du film d’animation  La Reine des Neiges , somptueusement interprétée par la superstar de Broadway Idina Menzel, prend le bon chemin pour devenir un incontournable classique. Voici une formidable pièce pour vos jeunesmusiciens.

Acclamé comme l’un des meilleurs dessins animés de Disney,  La Reine des neiges  est vite devenu un classique gr ce sa belle histoire, ses images éblouissantes et ses chansons extraordinaires. Cet impressionnant medley comprend  Vuelie, DoYou Want to Build a Snowman ?, For the First Time in Forever  et  Let It Go .

Il est rare que le titre d’une chanson décrive aussi bien sa musique ! Le méga-succès de Pharrell Williams avait été enregistré pour le film  Despicable Me 2  (Moi, moche et méchant 2), mais il connaît une deuxième vie sur internet, classé parmiles meilleurs titres du palmarès. Il suffit de l’entendre pour se sentir bien !

Employant non seulement des extraits de la bande sonore mais également les thèmes des chansons bien connues, Stephen Bulla a créé un medley puissant et stimulant rassemblant les meilleurs moments musicaux du dessin animé  La Reine des neiges ,parmi lesquels  Frozen Heart, Do You Want to Build a Snowman?, For the First Time in Forever, Epilogue  et, bien s r,  Let It Go .
Let It Go  du film d’animation  La Reine des neiges  a déj l’étoffe d’un classique ! La ballade entraînante a été mise en oeuvre par Michael Brown, un morceau rayonnant pour toute scène de concert.

Drums of the Saamis  dépeint la fusion entre les Premières Nations (peuples autochtones d’Amérique du Nord) et la province moderne d’Alberta (Canada). Les rythmes des tambours tribaux et une mélodie envo tante simulant la fl te en boistraditionnelle en sont les éléments fondamentaux. Au fil des mesures, ces deux piliers de la tradition évoluent en intégrant les échanges de plus en plus fréquents entre indiens et
sous_titre: The merger of the first Nation and modern Albertan cultures

description: Pour faire suite son populaire  Celtic Air and Dance , Michael Sweeney a arrangé deux mélodies irlandaises aux dimensions historiques :  Foggy Dew , écrite peu après l’Insurrection de P ques 1916, et  The Minstrel Boy , qui date dela Rébellion irlandaise de 1798.
titre: Celtic Air and March (Songs of Irish Rebellion)

description: Les turbulences et l’intensité d’une importante tempête de vent sont magistralement exprimés par Richard Saucedo dans cette tempétueuse composition. Un passage central vous permettra de reprendre votre souffle mais uniquement dans le but de clorevotre prestation par un final tumultueux et passionnant.

Composée la mémoire d’un professeur et ami bien-aimé, cette pièce touchante et lyrique pour ensembles expérimentés combine tendres mélodies et riches harmonies.  Stella Maris  est l’un des noms de Polaris, l’étoile polaire, dont le rôlesymbolique est de “protéger et guider”. Cette notion a servi d’inspiration pour cette oeuvre éloquente et gratifiante. (L’introduction au piano est facultative.)

Propulsion est l’action de pousser vers l’avant. C’est la force qui lance une fusée dans l’espace, qui pousse un coureur vers la ligne d’arrivée, et qui élance un dauphin travers les vagues. Avec des percussions acharnées, des rythmes énergiques,des mélodies dynamiques et une impression générale d’excitation,  Propulsion  traverse différents climats musicaux sans jamais perdre son impulsion implacable. Un tour de

Con una delicata orchestrazione e l’uso sapiente delle dinamiche, questo brano descrittivo appare più avanzato e più sofisticato rispetto a quanto potrebbe farci pensare il suo livello di difficolt .  Where Mountains Touch the Sky  è un poemasinfonico ispirato ai prati coperti di fiori della British Columbia nella stagione primaverile, cui fanno da sfondo le cime delle montagne ancora innevate.
Recorded by American Idol winner Phillip Phillips, this dynamic hit song was featured during the 2012 Olympics as NBC's theme for women's gymnastics.

Bringing to mind the scenic majesty of the northern forests, Michael's fresh-sounding overture for young players opens with a powerful fanfare before introducing the energetic main theme in 5/4. Carefully using repetitive patternscombined with a unique harmonic treatment and brief lyric section, this work provides musical depth in a framework that is easy to teach. (Grade 2.5) Dur: 4:00

Written in a driving fast tempo, this exciting work by Michael Oare incorporates the metric grouping of 3+3+2 as a recurring motif. At times superimposing layers of simple meter feel along with more complex patterns, Uproargenerates energy and excitement while using a variety of textures and colors within the wind and percussion sections. An impressive-sounding work for young players. Dur: 3:30

The term labyrinth refers to an intricate and confusing maze of pathways. In similar fashion, William Himes' somewhat devious, yet delightful musical representation takes the listener (and performer) on a journey of increasingcomplexity and musical twists and turns before ultimately revealing the familiar path leading to the exit. Composed using a single tempo, Labyrinth offers a unique and effective setting for

Written as a memorial, this beautifully emotional setting is a reworking of the traditional folk song The Braes of Baquhidder (also known as Wild Mountain Thyme) by Scottish writer Robert Tannahill. Samuel Hazo uses a variedtapestry of colors, textures and dynamics, taking full advantage of the depth and power of the modern wind band in creating this stunningly effective work. Dur: 4:20
sous_titre: A setting of Wild Mountain Thyme/The Braes of Balquhidder

description: From the stunning movie blockbuster Oz the Great and Powerful comes this distinctive and varied soundtrack from Danny Elfman. Featuring some of the film's lighter as well as darker moments here is a great sounding medley for band.
titre: Highlights from Oz the Great and Powerful

description: Commissioned by the Michigan School Band and Orchestra Association, this major work by James Curnow honors the memory and legacy of renowned conductor and educator Harry Begian. In consideration of Dr. Begian's Armenian heritage,Nulli Secundus (second to none) is a suite of three variations based on the Armenian folk song Cilicia (My Homeland). Movements include: I. March Caprice (concert march in fantasy variation

As implied by the title, the meter of 5/4 is an important structural component of this creative and energetic work for band. After the intense opening statement, a brief lyric and calm middle section builds to a full ensembleclimax before returning to the fast main theme. Blending extended jazz-like harmonies with an exciting rhythmic drive, this piece is sure to stir the interest of players and listeners alike. Dur:

Commissioned by the Sun City (AZ) Concert Band, In the Valley of the Sun is composed in a three-part overture format opening with a rollicking and rhythmic Western-style theme. The slow middle theme musically depicts the beauty ofthe Arizona desert with a flowing, yet angular melody. In the third section, the Western flavor returns to draw the work to an exciting and driving conclusion. (Grade 3.5) Dur: 5:50
titre: In The Valley of the Sun

description: Created in 1994, ReBoot was the first completely computer-animated television series and become a hit worldwide. The setting is in the inner world of a computer system known as Mainframe - a stunning universe where good constantlyfights the forces of evil. The powerful and dynamic score for the series was composed by Robert Buckley, and his wind band adaptation perfectly captures the cinematic richness and heroic

From the acclaimed composer of Paper Cut, Alex¦Shapiro, this unique, high-energy work could be¦described by the following: imagine Arnold Schoenberg,¦Henry Mancini, and Charlie Parker walking into a¦dance club in Havana, and staying for three minutes. Tight Squeeze ventures into new territory as it explores¦chromaticism and syncopation against a prerecorded¦percussion groove. The result is the repertoire's first

The Four Winds  by  Evan Hause  for Concert Band.   The Four Winds  is an homage by the composer to some of the well-known band composers, such as Clifton Williams and John Barnes Chance, as well as earlier wind masters like Holst and Mahler.  Evan Hause  was a student of William Bolcom, and his more advanced band work, Tango Variations, has been performed and recorded by some of the top university ensembles.   This
L’arrangement de Robert Longfield met le très célèbre thème du dernier James Bond 007, interprété par Adele, à portée de main de tous les jeunes musiciens. Que du bonheur !

Même si vous n’avez pas vu la série  The Pacific , nommée 23 fois et ayant remportée pas moins de 14 récompenses dont celle de la meilleure minisérie aux Emmy Awards 2010, vous reconnaîtrez sans nul doute le thème principal de labande son, coécrite par Hans Zimmer et Blake Nelly. Ted Ricketts en a fait une majestueuse version pour cor solo et orchestre d’harmonie.

Ce n’est pas seulement le clip provocateur de cette chanson, mais également la voix des chanteurs Robin Thicke, Pharell Williams et du rappeur T.I. qui font de  Blurred Lines  le tube de l’été 2012 dans plus de 65 pays. Au sommet desclassements depuis de nombreux mois, la célèbre mélodie R&B-Groove fera le succès de votre programme de concert. Divertissant !

Written for the 1973 movie of the same name starring Barbra Streisand and Robert Redford, this iconic ballad went on to win an Oscar for Best Original Song and to become a popular standard recorded by countless artists. Nicelyarranged for the concert stage. Dur: 2:40

Composed by John Powell, the exciting and emotionally powerful music from the DreamWorks film How to Train Your Dragon has taken on a life of its own. Here is an adaptation for younger bands by Johnnie Vinson that includesthe tender lyricism as well as dramatic heroic moments of the original.
titre: Highlights from How to Train Your Dragon

description: Composed by Alfred Reed in 1986, El Camino Real continues to be a repertoire staple for advanced ensembles. By shortening the duration and reducing the instrumentation and extreme technical demands, Robert Longfield hasmasterfully adapted this gem into an authentic sounding edition for younger players. A rewarding and distinctive work! Dur: 5:00

Although fairly brief in duration, this exciting overture features plenty of power and musical depth. Originally a work for brass quintet, it wasn't until many years later that the full band version took shape. Perfect as aconcert opener for mature players, this is a dynamic way to showcase your ensemble. Dur: 2:40.   Click to view score withrecording.

Here's a superb way to introduce your band to the joys of early instrumental music. Jim Curnow's well-conceived transcription is based on three 16th-century dances by Susato: I. Las Mourisque (Basse Danse), II. Mille regretz(Pavane), and III. La bataille (Pavane).

Le groupe pop anglo-irlandais One Direction a largement contribué la renaissance du genre boys band. Détenteur de la troisième place du célèbre concours britannique X-Factor, One Direction connaît une progression fulgurante dans de nombreux pays. Ce medley arrangé par Michael Brown, regroupe les titres  What Makes You Beautiful, Live While We’re Young  et  One Way or Another .

With an attractive blend of bluesy melodies and jazz inflections in brass, this unique and entertaining song from The Nightmare Before Christmas presents a fun alternative to traditional holiday programming!

Give your percussion section a chance in the spotlight with this appealing production number. With wonderful march-like melodies interspersed with feature spots for the drums, this is a great way to add variety and fun to yournext concert.

Featuring a relentless rhythmic drive and powerful-sounding themes, here is an effective and exciting piece for second-year players. Utilizing a single tempo and no syncopation, this is a great tool for teaching rhythmic securityand ensemble balance. Dur: 2:10

From the award-winning soundtrack from the hit movie  Life of Pi , here is the main song in a beautiful setting for band. Featuring exotic percussion and a mixture of delicate scoring contrasted with full ensemble statements,Teds arrangement ofthis haunting melody offers a unique and distinctive option for concert programming.

Even though the ranges and rhythms are quite modest in this beautiful lyric piece for young bands, there is a wealth of musicality to be learned and enjoyed. Delicate and sensitive in the beginning, there is a logical ebb and flowto the music as it builds to a full ensemble climax then back to the quieter texture and harmonic shift at the end. A rewarding setting for your young players. Dur: 3:40
titre: As Tears Fall On Dawn's New Light

description: Here is a solid, yet contemporary-sounding march for first year players. This powerful piece is carefully scored with interesting parts for all players. Dur: 2:15 (Grade 1)

In the style of a lively hoedown, here is an entertaining fast-paced number that's fun to perform and will sound great. There is plenty of built in contrasts in scoring dynamics as well as carefully placed percussion effects. Aperfect change of pace! Dur: 2:00

Even at the beginning level, Michael Oare shows that it's possible to provide creative music in a concise and appealing overture format. A stately opening leads to the exciting and energetic main theme. Perfect as a first festivalor contest number. Dur: 1:45 (Grade 1)

Sean O’Loughlin vient confirmer avec cet arrangement qu’il est tout fait possible pour un orchestre d’harmonie, d’interpréter du Heavy-Metal. Ayant joué avec les plus grands musiciens de studio et fort de son expérience de compositeur, il nouslivre une pièceremarquable rassemblant :  The Trooper  (Iron Maiden),  Iron Man  (Black Sabbath),  Rock You Like a Hurricane  (Scorpions) et  Crazy Train  (Ozzy Osbourne).

In what The New York Times' Allan Kozinn referred to as, "the hauntingly beautiful Ambient Air ... a set of vivid evocations of nature," Talma wrote four descriptive movements while in relative seclusion at the MacDowell Colony in 1983. Movements includes Echo Chamber, Driving Rain, Creeping Fog, and Shifting Winds. Featured on the Naxos American Classics label recording of the same name, by Ambache Chamber Orchestra

From one of the greatest musicals of all time, here is Bernsteins ever-popular Mambo in a carefully adapted and edited version that reduces some of the extreme technical demands of the original. This arrangement is notatedin cut time for ease of reading and is scored a third lower. However, none of the authenticity or energy has been altered, resulting in a stunning showcase for concert or festival, or even an

The magic of the holiday season is captured once again with the distinctive interpretations of Mannheim Steamroller. This beautiful setting of the well-known French carol will add a touch of serenity and splendor to any holidayoccasion.

Steven Spielberg's powerful movie brought us an equally moving soundtrack from master composer John Williams. Effectively adapted here for the concert stage, the amazing depth and range of the music is at times poignant and understated, and at times spirited and buoyant.
From the movie Home Alone 2: Lost in New York, this beautifully distinctive melody by John Williams offers a wonderful holiday option for your winter concert. Very nicely scored for young players.
sous_titre: from Home Alone 2: Lost in New York

description: This impressive work from Jay Bocook opens with a reverent and lush chorale segment interspersed with brief solos for oboe, flute, trumpet, and bassoon. The pace quickens with a grand heroic theme which evolves and intensifiesinto a majestic climax. The mood calms as this beautifully orchestrated and rewarding piece closes in a quiet and delicate manner. Dur: 5:45

From the final installment of the blockbuster Twilight Saga movie series, here is Carter Burwell's haunting and dramatic overture. This effective symphonic setting for band opens calmly and gently before closing with the powerfuland exciting fast theme. Beautifully scored.
sous_titre: from The Twilight Saga: Breaking Dawn - Part 2

description: Richard takes the listener and performer on an extended journey through various mood styles in this impressive work for mature ensembles. The stately opening strains gather momentum and intensity, leading to a fast-paced sectionthat features intertwining solo and small group fragments passed throughout the texture. An overall soaring theme adds a tone of triumph and grandeur throughout, and the final push to the end
titre: Beyond the Clouds and Into the Heavens!

description: Paul Creston was one of the most performed composers of the 1940s and '50s, and his music remains important and relevant today. His unique rhythmic and harmonic style is apparent in his piano work Five Little Dances. Robert Longfield's marvelous adaptation for band retains the character and charm of these delightful dances. Dur: 6:40

István Bogár's series of movements intended for youngsters is colourfully instrumented, evocative music, rich in melodic invention; in character it is most closely akin to Tchaikovsky's  Nutcracker  ballet music. In the opening movement ( Little March ), little boys wearing paper shakos on their heads and carrying wooden swords play at soldiers. The following movement,  Humming , is the only movement in the suite

Featuring classic mambo hits from Tito Puente, Perez Prado and Pablo Beltran Ruiz, here is a stunning symphonic medley showcasing this exciting musical genre. Includes:  Mambo #5, Ran Kan Kan, Sway (Qien Sera)  and  Mambo Jambo .
sous_titre: Mambo #5 - Ran Kan Kann - Sway (Qien Sera) - Mambo Jambo

description: The power and intensity of our ever-changing marine environment is portrayed in this descriptive work for young players. Incorporating a simple melodic motif along with syncopated rhythmic energy, Michael Oare effectively depictsthe power of natures most violent storms. Opening with a calm, yet foreboding introduction, the work quickly transforms as the storm draws near. Thundering bass drum rolls, driving rhythmic

Arranged here for flexible soloist and band, this sensuous melody from Argentine tango composer Astor Piazzolla provides a stunning showcase for Flute, Oboe, Clarinet, Alto Sax, or Trumpet soloist. Beautifully scored for band andcarefully paced.
sous_titre: (Solo Feature for Fl, Ob, Cl, Alto or Trumpet)

description: It Had Better Be Tonight  is from the film  The Pink Panther  and has also been more recently recorded by, heart throb,  Michael Bublé . This exciting version of  It Had better Be Tonight  expertly arranged by  Michael Brown , has a fantastic driving Latin pulse, powerful brass riffs, and rhythmic energy throughout. A show stopper for any concert band.

Enregistré l’origine par Cee Lo Green et rendu encore plus populaire gr ce Gwyneth Paltrow et les acteurs de  Glee , ce titre bénéficie d’un arrangement solide et divertissant pour très jeunes musiciens.
sous_titre: As performed by Cee Lo Green

description: Recorded by American Idol winner Phillip Phillips, this dynamic hit song was featured during the 2012 Olympics as NBC's theme for women's gymnastics.

Bringing to mind the scenic majesty of the northern forests, Michael's fresh-sounding overture for young players opens with a powerful fanfare before introducing the energetic main theme in 5/4. Carefully using repetitive patternscombined with a unique harmonic treatment and brief lyric section, this work provides musical depth in a framework that is easy to teach. (Grade 2.5) Dur: 4:00

Written in a single summer month while World War II was still raging in 1944, Prokofiev's Symphony No. 5 would become not only one of the composer's most celebrated and performed works, it would stand among the giants in all of 20th Century classical compositions. Cast in four movements, Prokofiev once gave a statement that he intended it as a hymn to free and happy Man, to his mighty powers, his pure and noble
titre: Symphony No. 5 in B-flat Major, Op. 100

description: First Choice  est une marche simple, légère et joyeuse avec une mélodie grisante. Un doux solo de basse et une partie trio enlevée forment le point de départ d’un jeu en syncopes qui ne manquera pas de ravir votre auditoire. Sans nul doute,  First Choice  se doit d’être votre premier choix !

description: One hundred years after the dedication of the Statue of Liberty in 1886, John Williams was commissioned to compose a fanfare for the re-dedication ceremony. At this event, Mr. Williams led the Boston Pops Orchestra in the firstperformance of this work, which the composer described as a group of American airs and tunes of my own invention. Performance time - ca. 4:15

Avec un rythme battant constant et des lignes mélodiques mémorables, cette ballade puissante constitue le retour triomphant d’Adele sur les palmarès de la musique pop. Cette version de Michael Brown reflète fidèlement l’ambiance ainsi que la montée en puissance du début jusqu’ la fin de l’original.

Bien que cette chanson du groupe emblématique Queen eut un accueil plutôt réservé lors de sa première sortie en 1979, elle est devenue l’une des plus populaires du groupe au fil des années gr ce, en partie, son usage fréquent dans des publicités, des films et la télévision. Avec ses aspects typiques d’une harmonie étroite et son changement de style dramatique, d’une ballade modérée un rock au tempo doublé, cet

Enregistré par le groupe pop américain Walk The Moon, ce tube rock enjoué a déj prouvé qu’il résiste au temps. Un arrangement réussi pour les plus jeunes instrumentistes, cette mélodie animée et amusante servira certainement de source de motivation pour votre orchestre.
sous_titre: as performed by Walk The Moon

description: Here is a very easy arrangement of the familiar music from Jurassic Park. Now even beginning players can enjoy one of  John Williams ' most iconic themes.

Recorded by Norwegian pop band  a-ha  in 1985, this familiar tune has taken on a life of its own, becoming one of the top selling singles of all time. Paul's  effective version for concert band provides plenty of variety in scoring and retains the exciting flavor of the original, including the signature half-time feel in the chorus.

A l’origine un groupe qui ne sortait que du surf commercial, les Beach Boys sont devenus plus tard l’un des groupes les plus influents des années 60 avec leur son particulier et original. Ce medley bien rythmé de tubes comprend  California Girls ,  Good Vibrations ,  Surfer Girl ,  Wouldnt It Be Nice?  et  I Get Around .
sous_titre: California Girls - Good Vibrations - Surfer Girl - Wouldn't It Be Nice? - I Get Around

description: Les films de James Bond semblent toujours inspirer de la musique extraordinaire et ce dernier volet ne fait pas exception. Cette ballade mémorable de Sam Smith comporte de grandes mélodies et des harmonies obsédantes. Une excellente adaptation pour orchestre par Michael Brown.

Le groupe pop australien INXS atteint le sommet de sa popularité dans les années 1980, pourtant son style particulier de musique dance et rock, ainsi que sa série de tubes impressionnante, reste aujourd’hui encore très populaire. Ce medley explosif des chansons favorites inclut  Need You Tonight ,  Devil Inside ,  Never Tear Us Apart ,  New Sensation , et  What You Need .

Written for the 1973 movie of the same name starring Barbra Streisand and Robert Redford, this iconic ballad went on to win an Oscar for Best Original Song and to become a popular standard recorded by countless artists. Nicelyarranged for the concert stage. Dur: 2:40
The Little Musician  (“Le petit musicien”) est idéal pour le premier concert de votre formation Junior. Une première piste d’exploitation pédagogique des éléments fondamentaux du jeu en ensemble.

In what The New York Times' Allan Kozinn referred to as, "the hauntingly beautiful Ambient Air ... a set of vivid evocations of nature," Talma wrote four descriptive movements while in relative seclusion at the MacDowell Colony in 1983. Movements includes Echo Chamber, Driving Rain, Creeping Fog, and Shifting Winds. Featured on the Naxos American Classics label recording of the same name, by Ambache Chamber Orchestra

Dans le monde des orchestres vent, Wim Laseroms jouit d’une grande réputation en tant que compositeur de marches. Ainsi, il a écrit Festivity, une marche idéale lors de tout défilé et qui donnera un air de fête votre programme de concert.
Juvenile Overture  est une œuvre lumineuse, éclatante de fraîcheur et de jeunesse. Le développement est joyeux et d’une insouciance toute juvénile.

Billy Joel began piano lessons when he was only 4 years old. At the age of 13 he discovered rock n roll and went on to produce countless hits in both rock and gentler styles. With this arrangement by Larry Foster De Haske has added on of Joel’s most beautiful ballads to the concert band repertoire.

Junior’s Choice  est une pièce entraînante et espiègle en trois mouvements courts ( Entry, Swing, Finale ). Les thèmes puissants et pétillants révèlent la diversité de la palette sonore des instruments vent.

The classic song  Stand By Me  was originally performed by Ben E King in 1960. Over the years there have been many versions of this and now there is one for wind band! This is sure to become a regular item on your concert programmes.

The bell like sounds of the trombone falling like golden raindrops introduce this piece for trombone soloists and concert band. During the piece the trombones are given the chance to show off the virtuosity of their technique and the work comes to a climax with a short final cadenza for the soloists.

Sound Variations is a work comprising of eight short sections, each based on a simple theme, each characterised by a great variety of styles and sounds. It opens with a fanfare-like introduction that soon leads into the presentation of the main theme followed by five variations on this theme. Each of these variations has its own style: Swing, Latin, Waltz, March and Rock. After a final repeat of the main theme, the

Virtuosi consists of a single movement divided into two continuous sections, each characterised by a particular mood. The opening section creates a serene and mysterious atmosphere with the clarinets introducing a warm, smooth melody which naturally flows towards a passage containing much ornamentation. This spirited work by Andre Waignein is based on a selection of French folksongs. It consists of three movements each characterised by a particular mood. From the energetic waltz of the first movement to the simple sombre structure of the middle movement this piece takes you through many styles and emotions and will become a true favourite with your band.

Concerto Dynamico is a sparkling work opening with a majestic introduction in which the whole band presents the main theme. The volume together with the broad melodic lines, create a robust opening that leads to a dazzling allegro. Syncopated rhythms produce a cheerful note, supported by the percussion. description: La chanteuse Alison Moyet est repérée au début des années 1980 par Vince Clarke, alors la recherche d’une plus grande indépendance : il a quitté son célèbre groupe Depeche Mode. La voix mélancolique d’Alison Moyet et la musique pop électronique innovante de Vince Clarke s’unissent au sein du groupe Yazoo dont des chansons comme  Only You  et  Don’t Go  rencontrent un vif succès. Quelques années après, Alison Moyet

With his street march The Easy Way, the Germancomposer Michael Friedmann proves that easy toplay music can indeed be worthwhile. Producing agood performance is, of course, always a challenge,even if the notes are fairly easy. This piece providesplaying fun for everyone!

Coast Life is an easy concert work composed by Johan Nijs and orchestrated for concert band. The three movements of this piece describe life on and around the coast. You can visit the bustling harbour, take a trip on the sea whether it be calm or stormy, or you can take a coast trip - either on the beach or along the promenade. All aspects of the seaside are portrayed in this attractive work.

During the course of the 20th century, the world of music underwent some significant changes. Every decade gave birth to new dances or styles of music such as the Charleston, New Orleans Jazz,swing, ragtime, rock and funk. Feel the Beat allows the band to sample this great variety of styles. This sparkling work opens with arhythmic ostinato in the percussion section. Nothing can quench the joy of life. Some playful

Sound Goes Round est une superbe pièce de musique légère dans laquelle Gilbert Tinner fait alterner des harmonies dissonantes avec des lignes mélodiques simples. Le résultat est solidement rock. Gilbert Tinner a défini le phrasé et les articulations de ce style particulier avec une grande précision. Sound Goes Round est l’oeuvre idéale pour compléter le répertoire pop ou rock de votre formation.

This is a real toe-tapping work with strong melodiesand a catchy syncopated accompaniment. There is acontrasting middle section with a lovely cantabiletune but the upbeat melody from the beginningreturns, to bring the march to a cheerful and rousingconclusion.

S’il fallait ne choisir qu’un seul adjectif pour qualifier cette pièce de Wim Laseroms, nous choisirions le terme de « varié ».  Variousity  développe une série de variations sur un thème donné qui apparaît sous différentes formes, dans différents tempi et dans divers chiffrages de mesure irréguliers. La diversité, un remède s r contre l’ennui.
Attractivo  est une œuvre entraînante, allègre, fluide et « sans chichi » dans laquelle les trompettes s’illustrent merveille. Bref, l’intermède idéal pour votre prochain concert.

Dans les années 1970, Elvis Presley s’est produit, plusieurs reprises, avec un orchestre disposant d’une grande section d’instruments vent. Caractéristiques de ces concerts : un débordement d’enthousiasme et une énergie intense.  Burning Love  est l’une de ces chansons au rythme enlevé où la guitare basse joue un rôle particulièrement important. Cet arrangement de Thijs Oud ne laissera personne de marbre.

La richesse du continent européen provient de la grande pluralité des traditions, et c’est sur cette pluralité que l’Europe du futur doit être construite. Cet hymne a été composé sous la Présidence autrichienne de l’Union européenne au cours du premier semestre 2006.  The Spirit of Youth  est dédié la jeunesse européenne, architecte de la paix et de la solidarité dans l’Europe unifiée de demain.

Cette marche fluide et légère possède tous les atouts d’une marche attractive : une introduction brillante, une ligne mélodique colorée et contrastante, un superbe solo de basse et un trio  cantabile  aux contrechants ornementés.  Corona  est sans aucun doute l’une de ces marches qu’il faut ajouter son répertoire.

Rudebox  est un des grands opus de la méga-star Robbie Williams. Parmi la longue liste des artistes ayant collaboré cet album, on citera les Pet Shop Boys l’origine du titre  She’s Madonna  (en hommage Madonna), une splendide ballade électro-pop, chanson-phare de l’année 2007.

Sir Eu  est une œuvre de commande conjointe du Comité Régional pour la Musique de Haute-Autriche et du Brass Band SoundINNBrass. Cette composition, taillée sur mesure pour le maître de l’euphonium Steven Mead, est d’une grande virtuosité. Steven Mead en assura d’ailleurs la création et la promotion sur les scènes du monde entier. Le titre fait référence la fois au dédicataire de la pièce et au concept européen.

L’auteur raconte l’histoire d’un enfant qui se livre des actes de cruauté pour tyranniser son entourage. Pour obtenir le soutien des démons, l’enfant répondant au prénom de Pruitt, invoque rituellement le nom d’une idole ayant l’apparence d’une mouche. L’idole finit par se manifester. Il

Un chef d’orchestre doit toujours s’efforcer de motiver ses musiciens et de garder une longueur d’avance sur son orchestre - voici la devise et l’inspiration de cette pièce. Pour Thomas Doss, la couleur verte représente la vie et l’espoir. Dans cette seconde symphonie,  Symphonie in Green  (Symphonie en vert), plus que dans la première, le compositeur s’inspire de rêveries philosophiques. James Horner's film scores are fresh, unmistakable, and timelessly melodic. This collection is not so much a medley of tunes as it is a portrait of his styles and moods. Incorporating selections from The Pelican Brief, Troy, and Glory, the piece is a tapestry of the dramatic and emotional cinematic textures only James Horner can provide. (4:15)

As a prequel to James Matthew Barrie's classic Peter Pan (The Boy Who Wouldn't Grow Up), director Joe Wright's fantasy adventure film is full of all the swashbuckling action and tender emotional moments that anyone who has read the book would expect. Included in this delightful John Powell film-score medley are the Opening Overture, Mine Escape, Pirates vs. Natives vs. Heroes vs. Chickens, Transfiguration, and

This exciting medley is guaranteed to make students and audiences feel as if they are in the middle of the chase to save the world. So get going and join the United Network Command of Law and Enforcement mission! Suitable for junior high and high school, three exciting tunes are joined to create this epic film score recreation that will provide an espionage adventure from beginning to end. (4:00)

This iconic film theme arguably has significantly contributed to the near-cult following of the genius of the Mel Brooks and Gene Wilder film. The haunting musical aspects of this piece are characteristically represented in the arrangement. Feature your trumpet soloist for a tremendous Halloween program or at any time during the year! (3:15)

Punk rock is hot again! Here's another hot song from 5 Seconds of Summer, an international sensation from Australia. It's laid back and comfortable, featuring a compelling bass line throughout the ensemble with a captivating melody. The repetitive nature makes it a snap to prepare! (2:15)
sous_titre: As Performed by 5 Seconds of Summer

description: Gaudete dates back to the 16th century, and was sung as a Christmas Carol throughout the monasteries of Europe. Meaning rejoice in Latin, this piece captures the intense passion of praise coupled with moments of calm reverence. (3:25)

Percussionists must learn both the rudiments and the scales. This piece provides the wind players some exposure to the rudiments. Paradiddles creates patterns played by the winds that mimic two types of paradiddles---the single paradiddle and the double paradiddle. This may be the first piece for concert band inspired by, and based on, percussion rudiments. (5:50)

The Vikings is not your traditional march. This dark, angry piece follows all of the traditional march concepts, including the standard form, repeats, key changes, and even a piccolo solo over the trio, but will provide a stunning change of pace from a standard march. (4:10)

Once in Royal David's City is a Christmas carol originally written as a poem by Cecil Frances Alexander. The carol was first published in 1848. This setting for young band augments the beautiful melody with textural contrasts and flowing countermelodies, leaving the seasonal feelings of peace and joy. (3:00)

This piece combines the best from the past and present. It is written in the traditional concert march from of the legendary John Philip Sousa, but with harmonies, melodies, and syncopated rhythms that give it a contemporary sound. A variety of soli sections make this a fantastic piece to show-off your entire ensemble.

sous_titre: from the NBC TV Film Project 20

description: From the critically-acclaimed fantasy film, Howard Shore's haunting and dramatic film score is arranged specifically for outstanding junior high and high school bands, and will be a welcome addition to your pop concert program. (5:15)

description: This delightful holiday arrangement is based on the well-known melody of God Rest Ye Merry Gentlemen. This fresh and exciting rendition of one of the most ancient of holiday carols will surely be a welcome addition to any holiday concert. (5:00)

from the Overture to La belle Galathee

description: Inspired by the Native American proverb, "We do not inherit the earth from our ancestors, we borrow it from our children." Roland Barrett has scored this original composition to musically reflect that sentiment conveying the inherent beauty, majesty, and grandeur of planet Earth. Combining fluid moving melodic components with energetic and driving rhythmic pulse, the work will capture the imagination of all. (5:30)
titre: And in the End It Was Earth

sous_titre: Featuring Sunrise - On the Trail - Sunset - Cloudburst

description: Written for the Young Band series and arranged by Victor López, this piece features "El Capitan," "The Liberty Bell," "The Washington Post March," and "The Stars and Stripes Forever"four trio sections of John Philip Sousa's greatest marches. You can never go wrong with a march, and this dynamic arrangement has four of Sousa's best. Bravo! (2:30)

This imaginative tone picture uses the Russian folk song, 'Meadowlands,' to evoke images of armies marching across the frozen territories of the North. The music opens quietly with snare drum and clarinets. Soon other instruments join in, as the armies approach each other, culminating in a battle scene that effectively utilizes the percussion section. The battle concludes and the armies depart, gradually disappearing

Based on the vintage Irish folk ballad 'The Minstrel Boy,' John Kinyon has given this passionate melody new life in a contemporary arrangement for the less-experienced concert band. To bring out its inherent sweetness and beauty, a sensitive interpretation and rubato tempo are recommended. (Grade 2)

titre: Atlantis: Lost City of the Ancients

description: The march for your first concert. Using only six notes and no eighth notes, this beginning march will make your group proud of their first performance. A moving bass line to challenge beginners, combined with a catchy melody and traditional march form, make for a perfect beginning band march. (Grade 1---Correlates with Unit 5 of Alfred's Basic Band Method.)

An exciting snare drum part creates interest for the percussion section. (Warning---You might be daffy after conducting this piece more than once!) (Grade 1)

description: Commissioned by MENC as the theme song for the Sesquicentenial Celebration of Music Education in the Schools of America, this composition was featured in concerts throughout the 150th celebration year. The band, orchestra and choral arrangements can be performed in any combination for special events and finales. (Grade 2)

Following a reflective introduction, the angular aspect of this contemporary work ensues. The percussion contribution to establish the pulse and drive with varied textures will make this work sparkle. Dramatic and bold this is an exciting addition to the contemporary literature affording opportunity for all sections to shine. A truly exciting choice! (6:00) This title is available in SmartMusic.

description: From the hip-hop rock kid from his In the City album, here's Kevin Rudolf's driving tune, "Let It Rock," that topped the charts for weeks. Built on the eighth-note pulse, the aggressive melody is introduced. You students will love performing what they're hearing on the radio. Cutting-edge pop for your beginners! (1:45)

The distinct percussive sounds are joined with the charismatic melody. Great opportunities for exploring rhythmic accuracy in a very musical work. A real attention-getter! (2:00) This title is available in SmartMusic.

The band commissioned the piece to honor its past conductors -- Earl R. Mays, Edwin S.Toporek, Herbert L. Day and John R. Spitler -- for their faithful service to education, music and musicians. The piece itself is a concert overture that captures the beauty and energy of

titre: Largo and Finale From The New World Symphony

description: Canadian composer Vince Gassi takes your young musicians on a voyage of courage and bravery with Flight of the Intrepid and its driving rhythms and heroic harmonies. A solemn lyrical section with independent melodic lines provides the perfect contrast to the dynamic opening and closing sections of this work. This is an ideal piece for your developing snare drummers, and is an excellent concert or contest selection.

titre: You're The One That i Want

description: Originally composed in 1890 by John W. Hawd, this Carl Strommen arrangement was scored for the centennial celebration of the Village of Mineola. The Algonquin term Mineola literally means a friendly and pleasant village. Mineola Waltz is a similarly pleasant work with a familiar-sounding melody and all of the flourish and panache of a distinctive waltz. This title is available in SmartMusic.

The flute section takes front and center to display their finger dexterity in this novel James D. Ployhar original tune. The flutists are sometimes overlooked as they provide the filigree to many instrumental works. Mix it up and let them be the focus of attention with this feature.

Dance of the Sugar Plum Fairy
Platoon Swims (from Flags of Our Fathers)

description: Featuring all four of the revered melodies from the film—We're Off to See the Wizard, If I Only Had a Brain, Ding Dong the Witch Is Dead, and Over the Rainbow—this suite is a great way for beginners to enjoy these cherished melodies. (5:30)
titre: Themes from the Wizard of Oz

description: Thomas Root's exceptional compositional skills combined with the use of some traditional sea chantys creates a very appealing composition for the young band.
The march from the 'Nutcracker Suite,' 'Bizet's Farandole Theme' and 'The Hallelujah Chorus' are effectively combined to provide a Christmas feature using well-known 'classical hits.' (Grade 2)
This appealing march captures today's sound and feel by incorporating contemporary melodic and rhythmic materials into a traditional march form. (Grade 2)

Maurice Ravel was only 24 when his piano solo 'Pavane Pour une Infante Defunte,' which translated means Pavane for a dead princess, became the rage of the drawing rooms and salons of Paris in 1899, but the work already held theunmistakable stamp of his style. description: Although it's been called a goofy novelty, this classic Todd Rundgren rock-and-roll favorite is perfect for your beginners. A hard driving rock beat with repeated eighths throughout sets the stage for a big sound in Bang the Drum All Day. Careful attention to the articulations supplied by master arranger Michael Story will make this the hit on your beginning band concert. (1:50)
titre: Bang the Drum All Day (I Don't Want to Work)

Originally intended as an analytical study for students in the composer's Advanced Harmony course at Louisiana State University, the piece seemed to demand further development as each new harmonic device was introduced. Its

Mark Camphouse weaves beautifully musical strains of the classic folk song in his Fantasia for concert band. This intimate and lyrical setting will challenge and inspire your band while exploring and celebrating our rich folk song heritage. (8:35) This title is available in SmartMusic.
sous_titre: on Black Is the Color of My True Love's Hair

description: Whitewater Journey takes both the performers and audience on an adventurous river-ride over foaming rapids and swiftly flowing currents. Midway through the trip, a gentle respite is encountered where the grandeur of the scenery can be appreciated, but soon the river again demands attention until the final destination is safely reached.

titre: As the Robin to the Meadow

description: Based on the chant Veni Creator Spiritus, Of Times Medieval takes your audience on a journey through Medieval Europe. Your audience will experience an ancient monastery, a celebration in the streets, and a clash of swords and shields. This bold and expressive piece is a must for any program.

For children, Hanukkah brings thoughts of a miracle from long, long ago and excitement each holiday season about what awaits. This new work musically conveys both reflection and joy with colorful scoring and expressive writing. Add wonder to your holiday performance this year with Hanukah Is Here. (2:35)

Take a trip to the Big Easy with "New Orleans Strut." Even very young bands will get into the groove of this piece, and the low brass and woodwinds will enjoy playing the hint of "The Saints" hidden in their parts. This Dixieland Jazz inspired piece is sure to be a favorite with young bands and their audiences alike. Correlates to Accent on Achievement, Book 1, page 19. (2:25) This title is available in SmartMusic.

This delightful band transcription of a Debussy piano classic is an ideal teaching tool. The piece will help teach tempo, dynamics, and rhythms such as the sixteenth-eighth-sixteenth pattern. The perfect selection for your next concert or contest. (2:51)

More Games! is a continuation of the composer's previous work, Games! Different games represented are tag, cloud shapes, and capes and swords. This piece, full of energy and child-like vitality, is sure to inspire your audience's inner-child. Get ready to play More Games!

Since 1919, Once in Royal David's City has been used to commence the worldwide BBC broadcast of the Festival of Nine Lessons and Carols on Christmas Eve from the University of Cambridge in England. Contrasting the pomp of a royal procession with gentler passages, this arrangement is mindful of the quiet eve evoked by the lyrics. Highlights include opening chimes and bells, a marching marcato section, and an ending

Campfire Sketches was inspired by songs of the old west-folk songs that pioneers might have sung while sitting around a campfire. The first movement, All the Pretty Little Horses, is a lullaby that is perfect for teaching legato playing and phrasing. The second movement, Cindy, is an up-tempo number in an old west style that gives all sections a chance to sparkle.

titre: All Is Calm ( based on Silent Night )
Upon The Wings Of The Wind

description: Everyone loves a round, and your audience will too when you put Rockin' a Round on your next concert. John O'Reilly has taken some of the most famous rounds and placed a fun rock-style beat underneath. Your audience's toes will be tapping in no time! Correlated with Yamaha Band Student, Book 1, page 12.

The sounds of ancient Greek soldiers doing battle are heard in this powerful original by John O'Reilly. The piece uses only six notes, yet sounds surprisingly sophisticated. Great fun and a great morale builder for your beginning band. Correlated with Yamaha Band Student, Book 1, page 10.

sous_titre: Bass Section Feature (Featuring: Jingle Bells / Dreydl Song / Jolly Old St. Nicholas)

description: Depicting the thrill of a hot-air balloon ride, Northwest Rising is yet another concert showstopper from Robert Sheldon. From the excitement of the initial liftoff to the quiet calm of floating in air, to the anticipation of the thrill of landing, this piece will take your band and audience on the musical balloon ride of a lifetime. Woodwind glissandi, refreshing harmonies and driving percussion help make Northwest

titre: Overture on an American Folk Tune

description: This energetic concert or festival opener is sure to make your band sparkle! Highlander is full of bright melodies for the woodwinds and trumpets juxtaposed with bagpipe-like drones in the low brass, calling to mind images of old Scotland. Generous use of the piccolo adds to the Scottish flair. A lovely woodwind chorale provides for an interesting contrast in the middle section, only to be interrupted by the exciting

sous_titre: Low Brass / Low Woodwind Section Feature

description: Steve Hodges creates a rhythmically interesting concert selection using nothing more complicated than dotted quarter eighth-note figures - perfect for your developing band! A syncopated low brass figure in 3/4 times serves as the foundation for the soaring melodies and countermelodies. Great for working on both legato and marcato playing, as well as on dynamics, articulations and key changes!

Close your next concert in style with this great patriotic original by Jay Althouse and Sally Albrecht. Scored for band with optional chorus, this arragement features a fresh treatment of American in 4/4 time and will provide a high-impact finale for your next program. Choral parts are available in 2-part, 3-part mixed and SATB voicings. InstruPax includes: director's score, 2 trumpets, alto sax, trombone [opt.
titre: Of Thee I Sing, America! (incorporates America)

description: This is not just another easy march . . . it's a work that provides a wide range of teaching possibilities for your students, including musical style and ensemble playing. This compelling and powerful number features an exciting interchange between the trumpet and percussion sections. Perfect for opening or closing your next elementary concert. Put your music program into orbit with Apollo March!

John Kinyon  has another winner with this transcription of the symphonic masterpiece ' The Moldau .' A tribute to  Smetana 's beloved river, this captivating piece describes the flowing and turmoil ofwater in musical terms. The parts are written well within the capabilities of young performers while keeping the essence of the original. This will add more than a little class to your next concert.

titre: Fantasy on an Irish Clogging Tune

description: The popular "Cortège" from Rimsky-Korsakov's opera Mlada has always been a great favorite in Eric Leidzen's classic band transcription. This engraved edition updates the scoring for the contemporary band and provides it with a complete full score. This transcription belongs in every serious band library. Duration: 4'40"

Dans les années 1960, le groupe Martha Reeves and the Vandellas compte parmi les artistes phares du label Motown avec Marvin Gaye, Smokey Robinson et les Jackson 5. Leur chanson emblématique  Nowhere to Run  a triomphé dans le monde entier tant pour l’histoire d’amour malheureuse qu’elle raconte que pour l'audace des percussions (tambourin et chaînes neige) qui enveloppent la mélodie de leur battement métallique.

Premier voyage, premier tableau : nous découvrons la Place Rouge, le Kremlin et le parc Gorki, célèbre lieu de promenade moscovite.
